    "title": {
        "rendered": "Facebook embed"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-black-color has-text-color has-background\" style=\"background-color:#eaf3f9\">Due to Facebook&#8217;s <a href=\"https://developers.facebook.com/blog/post/2020/08/04/Introducing-graph-v8-marketing-api-v8\">decision to close the oEmbed end </a>point for embedding Facebook links, the block will not work anymore after October 24, 2020. Publishers who want to embed Facebook links into their sites will require a developer account and an appid, and provide an authentication token with their call to the endpoint. Facebook Documentation:  <a href=\"https://developers.facebook.com/docs/apps/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://developers.facebook.com/docs/apps/\">create an app</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress leadership reached out to Facebook but it seems the policy change is final. Apart from alerting users here and in other places, WordPress contributors can&#8217;t do anything about it. </p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n\n\n<p><em>Facebook Embed</em> block allows you to add Facebook posts to your post or pages. Keep in mind that the post needs to be <em>public</em><strong><em> </em></strong>in order to add it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6-1024x467.png\" alt=\"Facebook Embed block\" class=\"wp-image-16361032\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6-1024x467.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6-300x137.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6-768x350.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6-1536x701.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image6.png 1552w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides Facebook Posts, you can also share links to Facebook Photos, Facebook Albums, and Facebook Videos.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note that you can not embed Facebook pages, Facebook events, and Facebook groups.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Embedding a Facebook post is as simple as following these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Copy the preferred link from the Facebook post you want to embed. Make sure it&#8217;s a public post.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"551\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3-1024x551.png\" alt=\"Copy the preferred link from a Facebook post\n\" class=\"wp-image-16361034\" style=\"width:347px;height:187px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3-1024x551.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3-300x162.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3-768x414.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3-1536x827.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image3.png 1675w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>From the WordPress dashboard, go to your post and click the (+) icon to open the block inserter pop-up window and search for the <em>Facebook</em> block. You can also use the keyboard shortcut <kbd>/facebook</kbd> to quickly insert a <em>Facebook </em>block.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"868\" height=\"588\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image9.png\" alt=\"Inserting a Facebook embed block using the keyboard shortcut.\n\" class=\"wp-image-16361035\" style=\"width:357px;height:242px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image9.png 868w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image9-300x203.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image9-768x520.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 868px) 100vw, 868px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Paste the link that you\u2019ve copied and click <em>Embed</em>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"324\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image7-1024x324.png\" alt=\"Embed the post into the block\" class=\"wp-image-16361037\" style=\"aspect-ratio:3.1607142857142856;width:397px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image7-1024x324.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image7-300x95.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image7-768x243.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image7.png 1492w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In your editor, you see the link and the comment  &#8220;<em>Embedded content from facebook.com can\u2019t be previewed in the editor&#8221;</em>.<br></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"690\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image1-1024x690.png\" alt=\"The message \u201cEmbedded content from facebook.com can\u2019t be previewed in the editor\u201d when you embed a Facebook post.\n\" class=\"wp-image-16361038\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.4816326530612245;width:397px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image1-1024x690.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image1-300x202.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image1-768x517.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image1.png 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Use the <em>Preview</em> button to see how the post fits into your post/page</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1004\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.49.15-AM-1024x1004.png\" alt=\"Preview of the Facebook embed post.\" class=\"wp-image-16017641\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:397px;height:345px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.49.15-AM-1024x1004.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.49.15-AM-300x294.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.49.15-AM-768x753.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.49.15-AM.png 1212w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block Toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"856\" height=\"218\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.51.37-AM.png\" alt=\"Block toolbar for the Facebook embed block\" class=\"wp-image-16017649\" style=\"aspect-ratio:3.932584269662921;width:397px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.51.37-AM.png 856w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.51.37-AM-300x76.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.51.37-AM-768x196.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 856px) 100vw, 856px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The block toolbar contains the tools to customize each block. The <em>Facebook </em>&nbsp;block\u2019s toolbar consists of the following tools:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Transform to</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"758\" height=\"475\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image10.png\" alt=\"Transform tool in the Facebook embed block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16361042\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.5947136563876652;width:428px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image10.png 758w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image10-300x188.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can transform a <em>Facebook embed</em> into a Group. This would give you the ability to change the background color around the <em>Facebook embed</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Block-moving tools</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"545\" height=\"155\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image5.png\" alt=\"Block moving tools in the Facebook embed block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16361043\" style=\"width:397px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image5.png 545w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image5-300x85.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the block-moving tools to move the block up and down inside the editor. Use the six dots icon to drag and drop the <em>Facebook</em> block and reposition it anywhere on the editor. Alternatively, click on the up and down arrows to move the block up or down the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change alignment</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"492\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8-1024x492.png\" alt=\"Change alignment in the Facebook embed block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16361044\" style=\"aspect-ratio:2.083798882681564;width:459px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8-1024x492.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8-300x144.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8-768x369.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8-1536x737.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image8.png 1552w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Align left</strong> \u2013 Make the Facebook post left aligned</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align center</strong> \u2013 Make the Facebook post alignment centered</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align right </strong>\u2013 Make the Facebook post align right</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wide width</strong> \u2013 Increase the width of the post beyond the content size</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full width</strong> \u2013 Extend the Facebook post to cover the full width of the screen.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <em>\u201cWide width\u201d and \u201cFull width\u201d alignments need to be enabled by the Theme of your site.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>More options</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"878\" height=\"236\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.59.04-AM.png\" alt=\"More options in the Facebook embed block\" class=\"wp-image-16017670\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:397px;height:97px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.59.04-AM.png 878w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.59.04-AM-300x81.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-10.59.04-AM-768x206.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 878px) 100vw, 878px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The block settings panel contains customization options specific to the block. To open it, select the block and click the cog icon next to the Publish button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"240\" height=\"58\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/image4.png\" alt=\"How to show the block settings sidebar\" class=\"wp-image-16361048\" style=\"width:274px;height:auto\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides the Advanced section, the Facebook embed has only one setting in the &#8220;Block Settings&#8221; sidebar: Media Settings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Media settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-2 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"406\" height=\"182\" data-id=\"12701737\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.46-AM.png\" alt=\"Media settings turned off in the Facebook embed block\" class=\"wp-image-12701737\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.46-AM.png 406w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.46-AM-300x134.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 406px) 100vw, 406px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"408\" height=\"197\" data-id=\"12701738\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.55-AM.png\" alt=\"Media settings turned on in the Facebook embed block\" class=\"wp-image-12701738\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.55-AM.png 408w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/04/Screen-Shot-2020-04-20-at-9.29.55-AM-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 408px) 100vw, 408px\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Via the <em>Media Settings</em> you can control the behavior of your post embed when viewed from a smaller device, like on a  phone screen. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Toggle switch turns on or off the resize functionality for smaller devices. The default setting is &#8220;on&#8221; or blue. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>&#8220;Off:&#8221;</strong> This embed may not preserve its aspect ratio when the browser is resized. In the off position the toggle switch is gray. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>&#8220;On:&#8221;</strong> This embed will preserve its aspect ratio when the browser is resized. The toggle switch turns blue in the &#8220;On&#8221; position. </p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Advanced settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The \u201cAdvanced\u201d tab lets you add CSS class(es) to your block. This will allow you to write custom CSS and styles to the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/HCaeEAd-xkijY3husAGN8FkRfOokz6h-mLa1vQoT11JIf366WEE4Y3jtoy6CTOJGTpBZELgZPdIewg2ug8pURV5XtFciGwLHJiNwleOvlGte5WnWTug0SYe4p-qBR54_8oR1NwHM\" alt=\"Advanced option in the selected Block\" style=\"width:397px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Advanced option in the selected Block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-very-dark-gray-color has-very-light-gray-background-color has-text-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2024-09-27\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated broken image Screenshots.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fixed inconsistent &#8220;Facebook&#8221; capitalization issue in the images&#8217; ALT texts.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-08-16\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Fixed formatting, updated screenshots, and added new information about block-moving tools functionality.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added ALT tags for the images</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-09-21\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Announcement of discontinuation of Facebook block in v. 9.0 and WordPress 5.6</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-08-18\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Replaced \u201cMore Options\u201d \u2013 new screenshot</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added \u201cMove To\u201d and \u201cCopy\u201d section under More Options</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-04-21\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add sentence to the Alignment about Theme support for wide width and full width options.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2020-04-20 </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
